Title: The art of writing structured code 
Date: November 28, 2025

<p>This blog is all about how to write clean and well structured code.</p>

<details>
	<summary>Formatting</summary>
	<span>Indentation:</span> <span>Use tab or 2–4 spaces consistently per level; avoid mixing tabs and spaces.</span>
	<span>Line Breaks:</span> <span>Keep lines ≤ 80–120 characters. Break long expressions.</span>
	<span>Blank Lines:</span> <span>Separate logical sections (imports, constant, functions, loop, conditional)</span>
</details>

<details>
	<summary>Naming</summary>
	<ul>
		<li>lowercase</li>
		<li>SCREAMINGCASE</li>
		<li>camelCase</li>
		<li>PascalCase</li>
		<li>snake_case</li>
		<li>kebab-case</li>
		<li><a src="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hungarian_notation" target="_blank">Hungarian Notation</a></li>
		<li>Mixed</li>
	</ul>
</details>

<details>
	<summary>Comments and Documentation</summary>
	<p>Explain why, not what.</p>
</details>

<details>
	<summary>Programming Practices</summary>
	<span>DRY Principle:</span> <span>Don't repeat yourself; use functions for repeated logic.</span>
</details>
